race.comment: STANDLEE (6) stepped out to a mile for the first time here nearly 3 weeks ago and finished a game third when searching for a hat-trick of wins. He gets a big swing in his draw this time, and with 4kg less to carry, he can bounce straight back into the winner's circle. SHOT DOWN BY LOVE (7) followed up her upset win here 2 starts back with a solid effort for fourth over this trip nearly 3 weeks ago. She drops 3.5kg in weight and should be right in the finish again. GLENRAY'S MATE (8) is a lightly tried 8-year-old gelding who is not short of ability when his mind is on the job. He gained a hard-fought win at Ipswich a month ago, and a similar run will take him close to winning this as well. BOLD TYRANT (10) had a rocky run off a wide gate here last time out, and should secure the right sort of trip from a superior gate this time. He is down in weight after a 3kg claim, and can figure in the top 3 this time. LUCONI (3) can mix his form, but is not the worst here.
